  "body": "When using the validator contract in QBFT the validators no longer come from the extra data but we still need valid extra data for the genesis block. We should a log a warning if there are validators in the genesis block extra data and we are using a validator contract so the user is aware the extra data validators aren't being used.\n\nIn QbftBesuControllerBuilder:validateContext could add another condition like this:\n```    \nif (genesisConfig.getConfigOptions().getQbftConfigOptions().getValidatorContractAddress().isPresent()\n        && !bftBlockInterface().get().validatorsInBlock(genesisBlockHeader).isEmpty()) {\n      LOG.warn(\"Using validator but genesis block contains signers.\");\n    }\n```\n\nExisting warning \"Genesis block contains no signers - chain will not progress.\" should only show if using validator header mode.",
